{
  "id": "36342f615aa946f0aa271f282b5218bf",
  "title": "Pragmatic Camera",
  "description": "Pragmatic Camera is a third person camera system that is easy to use and customize.",
  "longDescription": "<p>Playable Demo: <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1S23VBkOhlCm48flk-UeR1I_-VDpc2hlq/view?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://drive.google.com/file/d/1S23VBkOhlCm48flk-UeR1I_-VDpc2hlq/view?usp&#61;sharing</a></p><p>30-second video: <a href=\"https://youtu.be/_p4FltZb12Y\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://youtu.be/_p4FltZb12Y</a></p><p><br /></p><p>Pragmatic Camera is a third-person camera system that is easy to use and customize. It offers sensible defaults for a third-person game so you can quickly get to work prototyping or developing your game. The settings are easily adjustable through a Blueprint. Keyboard/mouse and controllers are supported. The core functionality is contained within a single Blueprint Actor component that can be applied to any character.</p>",
  "technicalDetails": "<p>Features:</p><ul><li>Thoroughly documented with comments.</li><li>Moves the camera farther/closer to the character, as well as from side to side over the shoulders.</li><li>Rotates the camera around the player.</li><li>Camera movements can be instant or smooth.</li><li>The following camera movement settings can be easily customized from a simple Blueprint property window:</li></ul><ol><li><strong>Camera Movement Style</strong></li><li><strong>Horizontal Camera Movement Style</strong></li><li><strong>Min/Max Camera Distance</strong></li><li><strong>Camera Interpolation Speed</strong></li><li><strong>Camera Horizontal Interpolation Speed</strong></li><li><strong>Camera Distance Change Step Size</strong></li><li><strong>Camera Horizontal Offset</strong></li><li><strong>Rotating Camera Speed</strong></li></ol><ul><li>Provides examples of multiple camera controls and how to set up the input events in the Character.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Number of Blueprints: 1</p><p>Input: Keyboard, Mouse, Controller</p><p>Network Replicated: The camera works in multiplayer.</p><p>Supported Development Platforms:</p><p>Windows: Yes</p><p>Mac: No</p><p><br /></p><p>Documentation: Documentation available in the Blueprint. Additional documentation is available here: <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/107ADElidVCzOVg7dz9WhiDv7vEvGWZVy-Z4HUUa77-g/edit?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://docs.google.com/document/d/107ADElidVCzOVg7dz9WhiDv7vEvGWZVy-Z4HUUa77-g/edit?usp&#61;sharing</a></p><p><br /></p><p>Important/Additional Notes: this asset is an actor component that must be used on a Character with a Spring Arm and Camera component.</p>",
